# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# Types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, test, chore, build, ci, perf
# Scope: optional, e.g. ui, platform, core, window, desktop
#
# Subject: max 72 chars, imperative mood, lowercase, no period at end
#
# Body (optional): wrap at 72 chars, explain WHAT and WHY, not HOW
#
# Footer (optional): BREAKING CHANGE, closes #N, refs #N
#
# Examples:
#   feat(ui): add double-buffered renderer with dirty regions
#   fix(platform): resolve termios raw mode on macOS
#   docs: update README with build instructions
#   refactor(window): simplify z-order management
#
# --- COMMIT END ---
#
# Rules:
# - Use imperative mood in subject ("add" not "added")
# - Don't capitalize first letter of subject
# - No period at end of subject
# - Separate subject from body with blank line
# - Use body to explain WHAT and WHY, not HOW
# - Reference issues/PRs in footer
